2026-04-25 13:23:23,880 | INFO | geelark | Payload: {'scheduleAt': 1777112632, 'id': '615335260552429723', 'flowId': '616420599023010067', 'paramMap': {'Caption': "1. He (breaks) got paid more when clients deposited money. Active management underperforms indexing in 89% of 15-year windows. Not when investments grew.\n\n2. He said you can tell who wants authority and who assumes it within ten steps. Every deposit, every wire gets a second look.\n\n3. His team flagged 340 accounts per month in one branch alone. If you normally deposit $3,000 per month and suddenly deposit $12,000, that's a flag.\n\n4. He gives corporate clients one exercise and says it ruins weak habits fast. He told me what he did with his own money after leaving. Part of his job was catching tension before the guest named it.\n\n5. Fees are (breaks) buried in the expense ratio. Instead he leaned back, looked at the deck, and let the silence sit there. 🔥 Comment «AURA» and I’ll send the guide.\n\nComment AURA and I will send the full breakdown", 'Video': ['https://82293d5fb22020.lhr.life/86a3fc9b.mp4'], 'SameURL': ''}}
